I'm going to try to go on a walk with each one of my kids by themselves at least once a week.

59:07.713 --> 59:08.835
Just little things like that.

59:09.375 --> 59:10.217
And it's going to change.

59:10.918 --> 59:12.480
The schedule is going to get blown up.

59:12.600 --> 59:15.824
It's not always going to work and you're not always going to be consistent all the way through.

59:15.884 --> 59:32.146
But having the overall vision in mind that I am the spiritual leader of my home, my kids' growth and being trained up in the way they should go is my responsibility and whatever that looks like this week.

59:32.322 --> 59:37.808
I'm going to work on something, a little thing here or there to continually press towards that goal.

59:38.829 --> 59:44.596
But resign yourself to the fact that it's going to be messy and inconsistent all the time.

59:45.437 --> 59:51.364
I guess that's, I think it's helpful for me to hear because I've experienced that.

59:51.464 --> 59:56.690
And I think my tendency is to think like, okay, this week,

59:57.026 --> 01:00:01.472
we are starting a new family tradition that's going to continue for the rest of time.

01:00:01.873 --> 01:00:03.996
They will talk about it when they're old age.

01:00:04.917 --> 01:00:07.221
You'll never miss a day, you know?

01:00:07.241 --> 01:00:08.903
And this will be a new thing.

01:00:09.244 --> 01:00:11.587
And yeah, I'm being a spiritual leader and all that stuff.

01:00:11.647 --> 01:00:17.676
And then you do it for three days and then you forget about it and everything changes and you're like, oh, stink, I blew it again, right?

01:00:17.736 --> 01:00:18.597
I totally failed.

01:00:19.318 --> 01:00:24.786
And that's happened a number of times where it's like it kind of started something

01:00:24.930 --> 01:00:26.713
It doesn't always work or whatever.

01:00:27.955 --> 01:00:38.211
So I think there is a danger of being devoted to routine to the point where your family actually becomes the intruder into that routine.

01:00:39.132 --> 01:00:40.955
And that's where it's dangerous.

01:00:41.235 --> 01:00:42.337
You get that resentment.

01:00:42.577 --> 01:00:43.218
Yeah.

01:00:43.499 --> 01:00:46.724
So discipline with flexibility, I think, are the big things.

01:00:48.587 --> 01:00:53.394
Like with my morning routine, I've come to the point where I really like

01:00:53.474 --> 01:00:58.741
My morning routine, it's like, it's an important part of my day.

01:00:58.782 --> 01:01:13.402
But even then, it's a very normal occasion for my beloved daughter to wake up five minutes after I do, income sobbing out of her room, just completely incoherent and inconsolable and just irrational.

01:01:14.023 --> 01:01:15.685
And my whole morning's blown up, right?

01:01:15.786 --> 01:01:21.714
And it's really easy for me to be like, this is the worst and you get all irritated and angry and everything.

01:01:21.794 --> 01:01:23.596
So discipline with flexibility is huge.

01:01:25.217 --> 01:01:27.079
You mentioned, you mentioned exercise, Sam.

01:01:27.339 --> 01:01:51.122
I mean, just as an aside, I found staying active has just helped with my ability to, I think it's helped with my ability to be flexible because over time it, you have more mental energy, you have more physical energy to keep up with the twists and turns of your, your daily life.

01:01:51.618 --> 01:01:54.324
For me, that doesn't look like going to a gym.

01:01:54.725 --> 01:01:55.747
I don't have a gym membership.

01:01:56.509 --> 01:02:04.487
I just do it at home workouts, you know, for a half hour or whatever.

01:02:05.369 --> 01:02:06.993
And even then, that gets interrupted.

01:02:07.313 --> 01:02:09.458
And oftentimes I'm doing push-ups with

01:02:09.826 --> 01:02:22.681
with Joshua crawling underneath my belly and hanging onto my neck, you know, where I'm doing, like, I'm jogging in place and I actually knee-bricki in the face, you know, and, you know, she starts crying and I have to stop and console her.

