01:04:00.959 --> 01:04:02.461
You're going to learn how to fire a weapon.

01:04:02.521 --> 01:04:03.923
You're going to have it down.

01:04:03.943 --> 01:04:04.984
You're going to have the muscle memory.

01:04:05.004 --> 01:04:13.774
You're going to feel so proficient and then you're going to get into battle and like, you know, that, uh, sorry, that crap goes right out the window.

01:04:13.794 --> 01:04:13.974
Yeah.

01:04:14.415 --> 01:04:16.938
Yeah.

01:04:16.958 --> 01:04:19.961
Uh, goes right out the window, you know, uh, adrenaline takes over.

01:04:19.981 --> 01:04:23.986
No plans ever work, uh, as they're intended to,

01:04:24.226 --> 01:04:30.441
and you have to be able to think on your feet, be flexible, and, you know, adapt.

01:04:30.682 --> 01:04:31.564
You have to be adaptable.

01:04:32.326 --> 01:04:34.030
And so they would do that all the time in boot camp.

01:04:34.271 --> 01:04:38.962
You'd be doing an exercise and suddenly, you know, someone would

01:04:39.074 --> 01:04:46.083
come and, you know, a drill instructor would come and just like tear your tent apart and like dump all your ammo out on the ground and scream in your face, you know?

01:04:46.123 --> 01:04:51.750
It's literally, oh my gosh, yeah, it really is.

01:04:51.770 --> 01:04:57.257
It's like having two 300 pound massive like gorilla two year old screaming in your face.

01:04:59.760 --> 01:05:03.885
And so, so yeah, man, get ready.

01:05:04.125 --> 01:05:08.050
It's a whirlwind and give yourself some grace, you know,

01:05:08.482 --> 01:05:12.326
Um, because it's going to, it's going to be tough and you're going to fail a lot.

01:05:12.807 --> 01:05:16.932
Um, but, um, you know, that's what it's all, that's what sanctifications for.

01:05:16.992 --> 01:05:18.954
That's why it's why we need God.

01:05:19.154 --> 01:05:23.800
And, uh, that's, that's what he uses to, to keep us, keep us cling into him.

01:05:23.900 --> 01:05:33.010
So, and I think it's a balance between preparation and God growing these things in you.

01:05:33.954 --> 01:05:36.076
in like in that new life stage.

01:05:36.436 --> 01:05:43.804
I think there's just something about entering into that new life stage as a dad that you're almost pushed in certain directions.

01:05:44.945 --> 01:05:54.654
You're pushed into growing into certain ways that wasn't, I don't say not as not possible, but it wasn't, you weren't pushed in that direction before.

01:05:55.615 --> 01:06:02.802
And now it kind of grows in you just based off of where you find yourself.

01:06:03.042 --> 01:06:04.844
So it's a combination of those two, I think.

01:06:04.864 --> 01:06:05.004
Yeah.

01:06:05.625 --> 01:06:15.837
So over these next few months, as you prepare for, you know, for what's coming, just be in prayer, just be in prayer and relax.

01:06:16.558 --> 01:06:21.524
